claim.claim-text:
1. A method of retrieving medical data, the method comprising:
receiving, via a user interface displayed on a user computing device, at least a first rule indicating types of medical data to be copied to the user computing device and a second rule indicating one or more of a modality, acquisition site, exam status, keywords in an exam description, or exam priority of medical data to be copied to the user computing device;
determining, by the user computing device, rights of a user operating the user computing device to view medical data of respective patients, wherein users have varying rights to view respective medical data based on at least their respective medical training and/or their associations with respective medical data;
selecting, by the user computing device, respective medical data for copying to the user computing device from a remote network accessible storage device in response to at least determining that the user has rights to view the respective medical data and the respective medical data matches the first rule and the second rule; and
initiating transfer of the selected respective medical data for display on the user computing device.

4. A method comprising:
receiving, via a user interface displayed on a user computing device, at least a first rule indicating types of medical data to be copied to the user computing device;
determining, by the user computing device, rights of a user operating the user computing device to view medical data of respective patients, wherein users have varying rights to view respective medical data based on at least their respective medical training and/or their associations with respective medical data;
determining rights of the user to mark the respective medical data as read, wherein marking respective medical data as read indicates that the user has completed observation of the respective medical data for purposes of creating a medical report, and wherein rights to mark respective medical data as read are based at least on the user's association with the respective medical data;
selecting respective medical data for copying to the user computing device from a remote network accessible storage device in response to at least determining that the user has rights to view the respective medical data; and
initiating transfer of the selected respective medical data for display on the user computing device.

5. A computing system comprising:
a first computer comprising an interface that can access one or more storage devices via one or more networks;
an application module configured for execution by the first computing system to:
determine, based on an identity of a user of the first computer, rights that the specific user has to retrieve medical data of patients; and
generate a user interface that enables selection of first criteria for retrieving medical data for use at the first computer, the first criteria including an indication of a frequency that the user would like the first computing system to poll the one or more storage devices to identify medical data matching other criteria including at least one of whether the medical data:
has been reviewed by a user of the first computing system;
has been observed for purposes of creating a medical report;
has an associated indication of urgency;
includes medical images;
includes images from a particular imaging modality;
includes a medical report;
includes key selected images;
includes audio;
includes text notes;
was acquired within a certain time period; or
was obtained at a particular acquisition site;


in accordance with the indicated frequency, periodically poll by the first computing system, without user intervention, the one or more storage devices for medical data matching the other criteria; and
automatically retrieve, by the first computing system, any medical data matching the selected criteria from the one or more storage devices.

18. A computing system comprising:
a first computer and a second computer each having one or more storage devices configured to store modules including software instructions and
one or more hardware computer processors configured to execute the modules, wherein the first computer includes
a first application module configured to:
access first rules stored on the first computer indicating rights and/or preferences of a user of the first computer to retrieve medical data to the first computer, wherein the first rules are configured specifically for use by the first computer;
access a first schedule stored on the first computer indicating one or more first times when medical data should be retrieved from one or more remote storage devices to the first computer;
at the one or more first times indicated by the first schedule, identifying respective medical data stored on the one or more remote storage devices matching the first rules, without user intervention; and
retrieving by the first computer, without user intervention, the identified respective medical data from the remote storage device and wherein the second computer includes a second application module configured to:
access second rules stored on the second computer indicating rights and/or preferences of the user to retrieve medical data to the second computer;
access a second schedule stored on the second computer indicating one or more second times when medical data should be retrieved from one or more remote storage devices to the second computer;
at the one or more second times indicated by the second schedule, identifying respective medical data stored on the one or more remote storage devices matching the second rules, without user intervention; and
retrieving by the second computer, without user intervention, the identified respective medical data from the remote storage device;

wherein the first and second rules and the first and second schedules are configured by the user specifically for use by the first and second computer, respectively; and
wherein the first rules on the first computer are different than the second rules on the second computer.

24. A non-transitory computer readable medium storing software instructions configured for execution on each of a first computer and a second computer operated by a user, the software instructions configured to cause the first computer to:
access first rules stored on the first computer indicating rights and/or preferences of the user to retrieve medical data to the first computer, wherein the first rules are configured specifically for use by the first computer;
access a first schedule stored on the first computer indicating one or more first times when medical data should be retrieved from one or more remote storage devices to the first computer;
at the one or more first times indicated by the first schedule, identifying respective medical data stored on the one or more remote storage devices matching the first rules, without user intervention; and
retrieving by the first computer, without user intervention, the identified respective medical data from the remote storage device; and
the software instructions are further configured to cause the second computer to:
access second rules stored on the second computer indicating rights and/or preferences of the user to retrieve medical data to the second computer;
access a second schedule stored on the second computer indicating one or more second times when medical data should be retrieved from one or more remote storage devices to the second computer;
at the one or more second times indicated by the second schedule, identifying respective medical data stored on the one or more remote storage devices matching the second rules, without user intervention; and
retrieving by the second computer, without user intervention, the identified respective medical data from the remote storage device;
wherein the first and second rules and the first and second schedules are configured by the user specifically for use by the first and second computer, respectively; and
wherein the first rules on the first computer are different than the second rules on the second computer.
